      "sc:citation": {
        "@id": "https://doi.org/10.18129/B9.bioc.BADER"
      },
      "sc:description": "For RNA sequencing count data, BADER fits a Bayesian hierarchical model. The algorithm returns the posterior probability of differential expression for each gene between two groups A and B. The joint posterior distribution of the variables in the model can be returned in the form of posterior samples, which can be used for further down-stream analyses such as gene set enrichment.",
